Node - Server side implementation of JavaScript.

npm init - Creates a package.json, equivalent to a Gem file in Ruby
JSON - JavaScript Object Notation, plain text hashes for data.

npm test will return that no tests are specified.
npm install jasmine-node  => gem install rspec
    -g => Globally install
    --save-dev => Adds dependencies to package.json (Gemfile)

Specify that you want to use jasmine-node for testing.

.gitignore the node_modules folder. Contains all dependencies within the project rather than elsewhere.

Within scripts (package.json):
    "test": "node_modules/jasmine-node/bin/jasmine-node spec/ --verbose"

Create a spec directory, create a Specfile.

Do 'reps' for setting up projects.

Within first test:
    var Game = require('../src/game');
    
Within source file:
    module.exports = Game;
